          // system as a labeled secondary source, prioritized for rural / single-
          // county members whose official floor-video record is thin. Each item is
          // keyed to the same roster id _issueEvidenceMap reads, carries an issueKey
          // that matches one of the member's tracked promises (so the promise's
          // evidence chip lights up with a "📘 View Facebook post" direct link), and
          // links the member's WebSearch-verified official/campaign page. The page
          // and its stated purpose are verified; the position described is the
          // member's own documented record. Impact is left neutral — this is
          // context/evidence, not a score-moving accountability driver. CONTENT_STYLE:
          // every item is about the individual's own record, never their party.
          // ── YouTube-source evidence (sitting Utah State Legislators) ───────────
          // First wave bringing verified YouTube video into the evidence system as a
          // labeled social/video source, prioritized for currently seated members with
          // the THINNEST combined evidence records. Each item links a real, dated video
