          // returned by YouTube itself), carries an issueKey matching one of the member's
          // tracked stances/promises so "Stance at a Glance" and Connected Evidence light
          // up with a "▶ Watch" link, and is graded automatically. A generic YouTube clip
          // is classified as a social/video source (NOT an official le.utah.gov floor or
          // committee record), so its Evidence-Strength ceiling is "Moderate." The one
          // exception is a high-quality, direct, long-form interview where the member
          // speaks substantively in their own words: marked with `interview` (see
          // _isQualityInterview), it is graded like a first-person record and can read
          // "Strong." Official/campaign channels and the member's own channel are
          // preferred; substantive third-party interviews, debates, and policy panels are
          // included where the member clearly speaks. impact:'neutral' — context, not a
          // score driver. CONTENT_STYLE: every item is about the individual's own record
          // and own words, never their party.
